President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key administration posts. Anthony Wilder Miller was nominated for Deputy Secretary of Education at the Department of Education. Miller has had a career as a General Manager and Strategist for top companies around the world. Mignon L. Clyburn was nominated for Commissioner at the Federal Communications Commission. Clyburn has been a member of the Public Service Commission of South Carolina since 1998. Juan M. Garcia was nominated for Assistant Secretary of the Navy (Manpower and Reserve Affairs) at the Department of the Navy, Department of Defense. Garcia was a member of the Texas House of Representatives and is currently an attorney. He has also served as a White House Fellow and is a Naval Aviator.